<section id="project-section">
  <%# flexbox div container in vertical direction that will contain projects %>
  <div class="projects-div rectangle quicksand">
    <div class="playfair-display">
      <h2>PROJECTS</h2>
    </div>

    <hr />
    <%# project 0 %>
    <div class="project-grid-black">
      <p>
        <strong class="red-color">KHADDAM,</strong> a mobile app that connects
        users with nearby skilled service providers such as plumbers,
        electricians, painters, and more. This app is built using React Native,
        Node.js, Express, PostgreSQL, and UI Kitten for the UI. Working on this
        project helped me strengthen my skills in mobile development, secure
        authentication with JWT, and RESTful API integration.
      </p>

      <p>
        The app supports real-time user login and registration, persistent
        sessions using AsyncStorage, and a dynamic bottom navigation bar that
        adjusts based on authentication status. I also implemented custom
        theming with UI Kitten and integrated a PostgreSQL database for user
        management. I am currently developing this app with the goal of turning
        it into a scalable solution for local service marketplaces.
      </p>

      <div class="zoomable" data-zoom-hint="Click to view">
        <img
          src="/images/projectsImages/KhaddamAppPreview.png"
          alt="KHADDAM app – main preview"
          class="gallery-trigger"
          data-caption="KHADDAM"
          data-images="<%= encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify([
      '/images/projectsImages/KhaddamAppPreview.png',
      '/images/projectsImages/KhaddamAppPreview2.png',
      '/images/projectsImages/KhaddamAppPreview3.png'
    ])) %>"
        />
        <span class="zoomable-badge" aria-hidden="true">
          <!-- magnifier with plus icon -->
          <svg
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
          >
            <circle cx="11" cy="11" r="7"></circle>
            <line x1="21" y1="21" x2="16.65" y2="16.65"></line>
            <line x1="8" y1="11" x2="14" y2="11"></line>
            <line x1="11" y1="8" x2="11" y2="14"></line>
          </svg>
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr />

    <%# project 1 %>
    <div class="project-grid">
      <p>
        <strong class="red-color">DEAL HEAL,</strong> a small web app that
        provides users with real-time deals on Steam games. This app is built
        using Node.js, EJS, JavaScript, Express, and the CheapShark public API.
        Developing this web app allowed me to enhance my knowledge of REST APIs
        by implementing the one provided by CheapShark.
      </p>

      <p>
        The API provides real-time data about Steam games currently on discount.
        The source code for this project is available
        <a
          class="red-color"
          target="_blank"
          href="https://github.com/yasloxamine/DealHeal"
          ><code>`click here to access the GitHub repository`</code>
