      <p>
        <strong class="red-color">MOROCCAN HORROR GAME,</strong> This is a
        work-in-progress game created using the Unity Engine for development,
        Blender for 3D modeling, C# for game logic, ambientCG for materials and
        textures, and ZapSplat along with Audacity for sound effects and music.
        I am currently developing this project as a hobby to gain experience as
        a coder, designer, and 3D artist. Through this process, I’m implementing
        Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) principles in C# and adhering to good
        coding practices, which contribute to improved game performance and
        optimization.
      </p>

      <p>
        The concept for this project is inspired by a nightmare I once had.
        While I don’t remember the details or the ending of the dream, I’m
        attempting to bring it to life as a 3D Moroccan horror game. Hopefully,
        I’ll give it a happy ending, something I didn’t have in the dream.
        Currently, there is no online demo available yet.
